[7]Pinus ayacahuite is native to the mountains of southern Mexico and Western central America, in the Sierra Madre del Sur and the eastern end of the axis volcanic transversal, between 14° and 21° of north latitude in the mexican States of Guerrero, Oaxaca, Puebla, Veracruz and Chiapas, and in Guatemala, Salvador and Honduras.
